<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 17 at 2:49AM CDT  by NWS Hastings</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of Polk County through
315 AM CDT...
At 249 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Osceola, or 19 miles southwest of Columbus, moving east at 35 mph.
HAZARD...Half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Stromsburg, Osceola and Shelby.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
